API

This Application Programming Interface (API) is the public interface for the objects and functions of our AAanalysis Python toolkit, which can be imported by:

import aaanalysis as aa

You can then access all methods and objects via the aa alias, such as aa.load_dataset.

Data Handling

aaanalysis.load_dataset([name, n, random, ...])

Loads protein benchmarking datasets.

aaanalysis.load_scales([name, just_aaindex, ...])

Loads amino acid scales or their classification (AAontology).

aaanalysis.load_features([name])

Load feature sets for protein benchmarking datasets from aaanalysis.load_dataset().

Feature Engineering

aaanalysis.AAclust([model_class, ...])

A k-optimized clustering wrapper for selecting redundancy-reduced sets of numerical scales.

aaanalysis.AAclustPlot([model_class, ...])

Plot results of AAclust analysis.

aaanalysis.SequenceFeature([verbose])

Retrieve and create sequence feature components (Part, Split, and Scale).

aaanalysis.CPP([df_parts, split_kws, ...])

Create and filter features that are most discriminant between two sets of sequences.

aaanalysis.CPPPlot([df_scales, df_cat, ...])

Plot CPP results at global or individual sample level as ranking plot, profile, or map (heatmap, feature map).

PU Learning

aaanalysis.dPULearn([verbose, pca_kwargs])

Deterministic Positive-Unlabeled (dPULearn) model introduced in [Breimann24c].

aaanalysis.dPULearnPlot()

Explainable AI

aaanalysis.TreeModel([model])

A wrapper for Tree based prediction models and Tree explainable_ai from SHAP package to explain prediction (typically binary classification) results at global and individual level

aaanalysis.ShapModel([model])

A wrapper for Tree explainable_ai from SHAP package

Perturbation

aaanalysis.AAMut([verbose, df_scales])

A class for analyzing the impact of amino acid substitutions on various property scales.

aaanalysis.AAMutPlot([verbose, df_scales])

Plot results of AAMut.

aaanalysis.SeqMut([verbose, df_scales])

Perform amino acid substitution for given sequence.

aaanalysis.SeqMutPlot([verbose, df_scales])

Plot SeqMut results.

Plot Utilities

aaanalysis.plot_get_clist([n_colors])

Returns manually curated list of 2 to 9 colors.

aaanalysis.plot_get_cmap([name, n_colors, ...])

Returns color map specified for AAanalysis.

aaanalysis.plot_get_cdict([name])

Returns color dictionarie specified for AAanalysis.

aaanalysis.plot_settings([font_scale, font, ...])

Configures general plot settings.

aaanalysis.plot_gcfs([option])

Gets current font size (or axes linewdith).

aaanalysis.plot_legend([ax, dict_color, ...])

Sets an independntly customizable plot legend.

aaanalysis.display_df([df, fontsize, ...])

Display DataFrame with specific style as HTML output for jupyter notebooks.

Metric Utilities

aaanalysis.comp_auc_adjusted([X, labels])

Compute the adjusted Area Under the (receiver operating characteristic) Curve (AUC) for each feature in the dataset X, comparing two groups specified by the labels.

aaanalysis.comp_bic_score([X, labels])

Computes an adjusted Bayesian Information Criterion (BIC) [-∞, ∞] for a given set of clusters in the dataset X.

aaanalysis.comp_kld([X, labels, label_test, ...])

Calculate the Kullback-Leibler Divergence (KLD) for each feature in X, comparing the distributions between two subgroups specified by label_test and label_ref in labels.
